KITTLESON: Mr. Berluti,

30:19.019 --> 30:21.121
we can stop this
proceeding right now

30:21.154 --> 30:23.356
and complicate
everybody's lives.

30:23.890 --> 30:25.592
There are rules of evidence.

30:25.626 --> 30:29.530
We will all play
by those rules.

30:32.599 --> 30:33.299
Mr. Webb?

30:33.867 --> 30:35.035
I'm done, Your Honor.

30:35.435 --> 30:36.970
Very wise decision.

30:49.850 --> 30:50.851
Hey.

30:50.884 --> 30:52.052
Hey.

30:53.987 --> 30:55.021
Did you fire him?

30:55.956 --> 30:58.058
Don't ask me why, but no.

30:59.092 --> 31:00.333
Maybe you like him.

31:00.366 --> 31:01.334
I do not like that man.

31:01.367 --> 31:02.669
It had nothing to do with that.

31:05.371 --> 31:06.973
You fired Jamie?

31:08.374 --> 31:09.342
No.

31:14.581 --> 31:15.549
How you doing, Eugene?

31:16.249 --> 31:17.250
Me?

31:17.283 --> 31:18.552
Fine.

31:20.253 --> 31:21.555
Okay.

31:26.159 --> 31:29.095
(door opens and closes)

31:30.997 --> 31:34.000
(overlapping chatter)

31:40.273 --> 31:41.708
What are you doing here?

31:42.075 --> 31:43.777
I just came in for a drink.

31:43.810 --> 31:45.445
I didn't know you'd be here.

31:46.279 --> 31:48.715
I'm here every night,
and you know it.

31:52.218 --> 31:54.755
You had the discretion
to let that stuff in--

31:54.788 --> 31:57.157
Get lost or I'll hold you
in contempt.

31:57.190 --> 31:58.825
BERLUTI: I'll risk contempt.

31:59.025 --> 32:01.234
That woman cries wolf
with rape.

32:01.267 --> 32:02.536
She set the whole thing up

32:02.569 --> 32:04.270
for her father to walk in on.

32:04.304 --> 32:06.239
Prove it in court, Jimmy.

32:06.272 --> 32:07.841
BERLUTI:
My client is innocent.

32:07.874 --> 32:09.209
You know it.

32:09.242 --> 32:11.177
That's probably why
you're in here getting drunk.

32:11.812 --> 32:14.080
Wrong again.
I get drunk every night.

32:16.683 --> 32:18.585
I know you, Roberta.

32:18.619 --> 32:19.720
I know your heart.

32:19.753 --> 32:22.556
I know your sense of fairness.

32:22.589 --> 32:23.857
This is something you can fix.

32:23.890 --> 32:25.859
Jimmy, you are a lawyer

32:25.892 --> 32:28.261
appearing before me in a trial.

32:28.294 --> 32:29.963
This is ex parte.

32:30.731 --> 32:31.898
After this case is over,

32:31.932 --> 32:34.367
if you wanna sit
next to me, fine.

32:34.400 --> 32:35.636
We can share a drink.

32:35.669 --> 32:38.004
Who knows? I might even
wet your whistle after,

32:38.038 --> 32:41.908
but for now,
get your ass off that stool.

32:43.944 --> 32:46.379
You're a vulgar,
desperate woman.

32:46.747 --> 32:49.716
All the more reason
to remain a good judge, then.

32:50.784 --> 32:52.619
Now, beat it.

33:10.276 --> 33:11.812
WEBB: You heard the victim.

33:11.845 --> 33:13.780
You heard from an eyewitness

33:13.814 --> 33:16.382
who saw the rape in progress.

33:16.416 --> 33:19.152
The defendant says
it was consensual.

33:19.185 --> 33:21.955
Consensual sex
does not look like rape,

33:21.988 --> 33:23.590
ladies and gentlemen.

33:23.624 --> 33:26.492
And consider the logic
of what the defendant

33:26.527 --> 33:28.194
is asking you to believe,

33:28.228 --> 33:31.064
that Jessica Palmer
picked up a strange man,

33:31.097 --> 33:31.832
a felon,

33:31.865 --> 33:34.234
in a terrible section of town,

33:34.267 --> 33:35.501
brought him back to her place

33:35.536 --> 33:39.239
to have unprotected sex,
all the while knowing

33:39.272 --> 33:41.274
her father would either be there

33:41.307 --> 33:42.743
or be there shortly.

33:43.109 --> 33:44.578
That really...

33:44.611 --> 33:46.613
sounds credible,
doesn't it?

33:47.447 --> 33:50.584
And what would be her motive
for making this up?

33:51.818 --> 33:54.320
Because rape trials are fun?

33:56.657 --> 33:58.925
The eyewitness was her father,

33:58.959 --> 34:01.234
who basically admitted
he went into shock

34:01.267 --> 34:02.769
as soon as
he entered the room.

34:02.803 --> 34:05.071
Can we completely trust
his version

34:05.105 --> 34:06.973
of what he thinks he saw?

34:07.440 --> 34:08.574
No.

34:08.609 --> 34:12.846
This case comes down
to Jessica Palmer's word

34:12.879 --> 34:14.313
against Derrick Mills.

34:14.347 --> 34:16.949
Might you be more
inclined to believe her?

34:16.983 --> 34:19.820
Sure. Okay.

34:19.853 --> 34:22.355
But can we know
she's telling the truth

34:22.388 --> 34:25.091
beyond all reasonable doubt?

34:25.491 --> 34:27.327
And you wanna talk
about logic?

34:27.360 --> 34:30.163
My client's prints
were all over the car,

34:30.196 --> 34:31.496
all over the house.

34:31.532 --> 34:32.899
He's got a record.

34:32.933 --> 34:35.835
His prints are on file
with the police.

34:35.869 --> 34:37.036
He's gonna rape somebody

34:37.070 --> 34:40.106
and leave that kind of
evidence behind?

34:40.139 --> 34:41.507
He's gonna leave his semen there

34:41.542 --> 34:43.744
for easy DNA identification?

34:43.777 --> 34:46.012
Does that make sense to you?

34:46.045 --> 34:49.215
Something's going on here,
folks.

34:50.016 --> 34:51.217
The D. A. asks,

34:51.251 --> 34:53.119
"What would be her motive
to lie?"

34:53.987 --> 34:55.621
We can't know.

34:55.656 --> 34:57.090
We have rape shield laws

34:57.123 --> 35:00.567
that prohibit us
from getting into her story,

35:01.702 --> 35:03.770
but let me ask you this,

35:03.804 --> 35:06.973
does it feel like
you've got the whole story?

35:08.274 --> 35:09.576
Does it?

35:21.888 --> 35:23.189
Are you not going to work today?

35:23.957 --> 35:25.559
I am. I just thought I might...

35:25.592 --> 35:27.093
hover a bit this morning.

35:30.664 --> 35:32.332
What are you thinking?

35:33.600 --> 35:35.168
Why does everybody so readily

35:35.201 --> 35:36.970
ask that question today?

35:37.003 --> 35:39.139
It's as common as
"How's the weather?"

35:40.206 --> 35:41.474
It's cheating.

35:41.508 --> 35:44.477
People should be required
to figure it out.

35:51.017 --> 35:53.253
Has a man ever asked you
to disrobe?

35:55.188 --> 35:56.222
I don't mean go to bed.

35:56.256 --> 35:58.525
I mean,
simply asked you to disrobe

35:58.559 --> 36:01.234
from across the room
so he might look at you?

36:02.402 --> 36:03.570
No.

36:04.170 --> 36:05.772
Would you like
to be asked that?

36:07.941 --> 36:09.075
I don't know.

36:10.176 --> 36:12.145
Like I said,
I've never been asked.

36:13.847 --> 36:15.682
Would you like to be asked?

36:18.785 --> 36:19.986
Yes.

36:21.655 --> 36:22.923
Interesting.

36:34.835 --> 36:37.538
If you think I'm asking
only because you want me to,

36:37.571 --> 36:40.674
I assure you,
I'm being genuine.

36:44.244 --> 36:46.412
Would you take off your robe?

36:48.782 --> 36:51.785
(music playing)

37:20.987 --> 37:22.355
How long have they been out?

37:23.824 --> 37:25.491
Almost five hours,

37:25.526 --> 37:27.594
which my guess it's good.

37:28.261 --> 37:31.064
It means they at least got
to be asking questions.

37:31.397 --> 37:32.666
Yeah.

37:32.699 --> 37:34.134
Can I talk to you
for a second?

37:46.780 --> 37:49.850
It was in the file that she had
claimed rape before?

37:54.420 --> 37:55.622
So if you had filed
your questions

37:55.656 --> 37:57.490
with the court
as required,

37:57.524 --> 37:58.825
you probably would've been able

37:58.859 --> 38:00.200
to cross-examine
the victim on it.

38:00.233 --> 38:03.136
You don't need
to tell me, okay?

38:03.870 --> 38:06.239
You and I both know

38:06.272 --> 38:08.575
the idea that every defendant

38:08.609 --> 38:10.744
is entitled
to an adequate defense...

38:10.777 --> 38:11.578
is a lie.

38:12.679 --> 38:14.414
Defense lawyers many times

38:14.447 --> 38:16.416
barely bother
to meet the client

38:16.449 --> 38:17.350
or read the files.

38:17.383 --> 38:19.219
Some even doze during trials.

38:19.252 --> 38:21.922
Lawyers phone it in
all the time,

38:21.955 --> 38:23.256
but for it to happen here,

38:24.858 --> 38:26.392
for a lawyer in this firm

38:26.426 --> 38:29.095
to be as blatantly unprepared,

38:29.129 --> 38:31.431
court-appointed or not--

38:31.464 --> 38:33.800
If we lose,

38:33.834 --> 38:38.138
I'll prepare the inadequate
defense appeal myself.

38:40.406 --> 38:43.409
(phone ringing)

38:46.346 --> 38:47.480
Yeah?

38:49.015 --> 38:50.216
Okay.

38:52.085 --> 38:53.554
Your jury's back.

38:56.122 --> 38:58.592
(music playing)

38:58.625 --> 39:00.701
KITTLESON:
Will the defendant please rise?

39:06.439 --> 39:08.909
Members of the jury,
have you reached a verdict?

39:09.843 --> 39:10.744
We have, Your Honor.

39:12.746 --> 39:13.914
What say you?

39:15.048 --> 39:16.650
Commonwealth
versus Derrick Mills,

39:16.683 --> 39:19.252
on the charge
of forcible rape,

39:19.953 --> 39:22.589
we find the defendant,
Derrick Mills...

39:23.724 --> 39:24.457
guilty.

39:27.661 --> 39:29.162
KITTLESON:
This concludes your service.

39:29.462 --> 39:30.964
The court thanks you.

39:30.997 --> 39:32.933
Security will take
the defendant into custody.

39:34.167 --> 39:35.001
We are adjourned.

39:35.035 --> 39:36.402
(gavel bangs)

39:36.436 --> 39:39.439
(overlapping chatter)

39:41.842 --> 39:42.843
Derrick,

39:45.378 --> 39:46.513
Derrick, look at me.

39:49.415 --> 39:51.585
I will get you out.

39:51.618 --> 39:53.920
Whatever I have to do,

39:53.954 --> 39:55.889
I will get you out.

40:01.668 --> 40:03.236
(sighs)

40:04.638 --> 40:07.641
(music playing)

40:31.264 --> 40:32.833
Where's Jimmy now?

40:32.866 --> 40:34.968
WILSON: He went home.

40:35.001 --> 40:36.603
He's pretty devastated.

40:36.637 --> 40:38.805
Call him. He needs to get
to work on the appeal.

40:38.839 --> 40:41.474
Eugene, I should've
caught this, too.

40:41.875 --> 40:43.777
Yes, you should have,

40:43.810 --> 40:45.812
but you're a third-year
law student.

40:45.846 --> 40:46.947
He's not.

40:50.416 --> 40:52.318
You're not gonna ask me
for my thoughts, are you?

40:56.823 --> 40:57.490
Eugene,

40:59.626 --> 41:00.834
Ellenor said something
about me

41:00.867 --> 41:02.268
being self-destructive.

41:02.302 --> 41:04.370
It was probably
just conversation filler,

41:04.404 --> 41:06.540
I really don't know.

41:06.573 --> 41:07.974
But I assure you,

41:08.008 --> 41:11.144
if I am unwittingly
or unconsciously

41:11.177 --> 41:13.714
trying to take anybody down,

41:13.747 --> 41:15.582
it isn't you

41:15.616 --> 41:17.283
or this law firm.

41:26.492 --> 41:28.261
(glass clinking)

41:28.294 --> 41:30.330
KITTLESON: You're on my stool.

41:38.071 --> 41:38.839
I'm sorry.

41:39.873 --> 41:41.808
Your ruling was correct.

41:43.109 --> 41:44.310
And any--

41:46.513 --> 41:49.015
this was my doing.

41:49.049 --> 41:51.184
I just came to say that.

41:55.956 --> 41:58.291
Now that the case is over,
I was...

41:58.324 --> 42:00.233
wondering if your offer
is still good.

42:03.169 --> 42:05.338
I mean,
to have a drink together.

42:06.339 --> 42:09.209
The case isn't over.

42:09.242 --> 42:11.011
There's still sentencing.

42:14.480 --> 42:16.249
But I suppose
there's nothing wrong

42:16.282 --> 42:19.252
in drinking separately
on adjacent stools,

42:20.286 --> 42:24.057
enjoying the illusion
of company, I guess.

42:27.694 --> 42:29.295
I could use it.

42:33.433 --> 42:35.168
So could I.

42:35.201 --> 42:38.204
(music playing)

43:01.301 --> 43:04.337
(music playing)

43:27.728 --> 43:28.695
WOMAN: You stinker.

43:28.729 --> 43:31.532
(music playing)
